                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/12560.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of War</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">War Department</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 18, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Secretary of War presents his compliments to the Honorable the Secretary of
                    State and quotes, for his information, the following telegram from the
                    Commanding General at Vera Cruz, dated July 17, 1914: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Huerta, Blanquet and party reached Puerto Mexico 8.15 this evening.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
            </div>
